<aura:documentation>
	<aura:description>
    	General Description : 

		Json needs to be setup as followed and is initialized with default values, 
        if removed then will be set to default on rendering of component. If set 
        link_flag to false then the url related fields are optional.
        default json, use as template but do not change field names.
        Set as attribute of parent component and set as attribute in 
        component tag like so et4ae5:step_modal step_json="v.jsonName" where attribute 
		is like so : aura:attribute name="step_json" type="json" set json 
        in helper of parent application/component on initialization.<br/>

        <b>Field definitions :</b><br/>
 
		title       - header of component<br/>
		body        - Content of modal on each page.<br/>
        
        <b>JSON template :</b><pre>
{
    "entries" : [
        {
            "title" : "TITLE",
            "body"  : "Content in HTML"
        },
        {
            "title" : "TITLE",
            "body"  : "Content in HTML"
        }
    ]
}</pre>
        <p><b>Style considerations:</b></p>
        <ul>
            <li>The component modal window can be styled using the .modal1, .modal-dialog1, .modal-content1, .modal-header1, .modal-body1 and .modal-footer1 classes</li>
        </ul>
    </aura:description>
    <aura:example name="step_modal" ref="et4ae5:step_modal" label="Label">
		This is using no values and must be passed a JSON value!
	</aura:example>
</aura:documentation>